result.name: Wai Kee Noodle Cafe

reviews.text: my favourite place to eat in sham shu po classic place must try there popular pigs liver noodle soap and ka Yun kaya French toast and a cup of ice lemon tea mhhh mhhh mhhh :)

Great spot for a quick bite. I enjoy the pork liver the most. Tip: If coming in a party of two, I like to each order a different one-topping noodle, then share half the toppings—you get the best price this way! The french toast is really great! But you might want to share it if you haven’t got a big stomach. Definitely a staple for me in SSP!
One of my favourite pig liver noodle in Hong Kong, although it is not healthy but definitely should try!
The pig liver and beef noodle is the signature dishes where you will not be disappointed if you are a pig liver lover. It will taste even better if pepper is added.

Cannot be more local.. Very popular and famous restaurant in Sham Shui Po. Everybody come here to eat organs noodles soup.
Try the Kaya toast too it's very good (a bit sweet).
